@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"
---<Introduction to REN_Statz>---

  This door was requested by S.n.s (sysop of Skullmonkey BBS), as he 
  thought he'd quite like to see who his best callers/uploaders/leachers
  are!.

  REN_Statz has become known as `The Hall of Fame' Door by those who
  use it :-)

@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
@node INSTALLATION "Installation"
---<Installing REN_Statz>---

  Simply Unarchive the REN_Statz Archive to your DOORS: Path. This is
  done by using one of the Amiga's standard Archivers...

      CLI> C:LhA x REN_Statz.lha DOORS:

  The Archive will automatically create the `REN_Statz' Directory within
  your BBS Doors Directory.

  Now, To use REN_Statz, You will need any version of the `MAXsBBS'
  BBS System. This can be obtained from Aminet or from any decent BBS!

  You can either setup this Door as a MAXs Menu item or as a Logon Door
  using the `IntroDoor.Text' or `MainDoor.Text' files.

  -<MAXsBBS Menu Item>-

  Now, Simply load up your copy of MAXsBBS Professional, and go to the
  `Menu Editor' Window...

  Locate the Menu in which you want to use the REN_Statz Door....

  Change the Menus to read...
  in MaxsBBS 1.54 :-

  Key  Function  Extra  Lo Acc  Hi Acc  Path/Filename/Extra...
    ?        34      0       ?       ?  DOORS:REN_Statz/REN_Statz

  or in MaxsPro :-
    ?        34      0       ?       ?  DOORS:REN_Statz/REN_Statz + 

  The `Key', `Lo Acc' and `Hi Acc' figures can be whatever you wish as
  these figures are upto the SysOp of the BBS.

  Please, DO NOT FORGET to add the `+' (Plus) sign at the End of the
  `Path/Filename/Extra...' Gadget as this tells REN_Statz that you are
  using MAXsBBS Professional.

  -<Door Scripts>-

  Load any of the Door Scripts `IntroDoor.Text', `MainDoor.Text',
  and add the following line to wherever you want REN_Statz to be 
  launched from...

  REN_Statz/REN_Statz

  or

  REN_Statz/REN_Statz +     (For MaxsPro)

  Now, Save the Door Script...


@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
@node CONFIGURATION "Configuration"
---<Configuring REN_Statz>---

No configuration available with this version.

You could replace the ANSI title bar to suit your BBS.
 
@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
@node USAGE "Usage"
---<Using REN_Statz>---

  REN_Statz consists of ONE Main Executable...

  When the Door loads, it displays the Hall of Fame stats!

  Now, Simply press ANY KEY to return to the BBS.

@{"< >" Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu
@endnode
